    <tr> 
     <td valign="top" height="723"> <b>About the Program</b> <p>Geoscience Policy engages in a variety of legislative review and advocacy activities. </p> 
      <ul> 
       <li><b><a href="gapac.html">Geoscience Policy Committee</a></b></li> 
       <li><b><a href="http://www.agiweb.org/gapac/plan998.html">Geoscience Policy Strategic Plan</a></b> </li> 
      </ul> <p><strong> Staff</strong></p> <p>Maeve Boland<br> Director, Geoscience Policy<br> Tel.: +1 (703)-379-2480 x 228<br> <a href="mailto:mboland@agiweb.org">mboland@agiweb.org</a><br> </p> <p>Abby Seadler<br> Geoscience Policy Associate<br> Tel.: +1 (703) 379-2480 x 204<br> <a href="mailto:aseadler@agiweb.org ">aseadler@agiweb.org </a><br> <a href="https://twitter.com/agigap">https://twitter.com/agigap</a><br> <img src="/graphics/blueline.gif" width="405" height="5" vspace="10"><br> <b><a href="../resources/letterstolawmakers.html">Letters to Lawmakers</a></b><br> <img src="/graphics/blueline.gif" width="405" height="5" vspace="10"><br> <b><a href="../testimony/testimony.html">Testimony Submitted to Congress</a></b><br> <img src="/graphics/blueline.gif" width="405" height="5" vspace="10"><br> <b><a href="../resources/positionstatements.html">AGI and Member Society Position Statements</a></b><br> <img src="/graphics/blueline.gif" width="405" height="5" vspace="10"><br> <b><a name="coalitions"></a>Coalitions</b> </p> <p>AGI advocates on behalf of the geosciences by building alliances with organizations committed to similar policy objectives. AGI is an active member of the following groups: </p> 
      <ul class="style3"> 
       <li><a href="http://www.hazardscaucus.org" class="linkhead">Congressional Hazards Caucus Alliance</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://www.usgscoalition.org/" class="linkhead">USGS Coalition</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://www.cnsfweb.org/" class="linkhead">Coalition for National Science Funding</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://www.aps.org/policy/tools/coalitions/esc/">Energy Sciences Coalition</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://www.stemedcoalition.org/" class="linkhead">Science Technology Engineering and Math (STEM) Education Coalition</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://shr.aaas.org/coalition/index.shtml">Science and Human Rights Coalition</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://www.researchcaucus.org/" class="linkhead">R&amp;D Caucus Advisory Committee</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://www.nehrp.org/">National Earthquake Hazards Reduction Program Coalition</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://www.friendsofnoaa.org/Default.htm">Friends of NOAA</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://www.setcvd.org/">Science-Engineering-Technology (SET) Working Group</a></li> 
       <li><a href="http://www.copusproject.org/">Coalition on the Public Understanding of Science</a></li> 
       <li>National Conference of State Legislators Geology Consortium</li> 
       <li>Evolution Task Force</li> 
       <li>Law of the Sea Ratification Group</li> 
       <li>National Land Imaging Program Coalition</li> 
      </ul> <p><img src="/graphics/blueline.gif" width="405" height="5" vspace="10"><br> <strong><a href="../events/index.html">Events</a></strong><br> <img src="/graphics/blueline.gif" alt="" width="405" height="5" vspace="10"><br> </p> </td> 
    </tr> 
